{"type":"message","id":"30fecf22","parentId":"92119703","timestamp":"2026-02-23T11:43:42.723Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" The user is asking me to check whether the `context-anchor` skill is applicable for me given my current QMD memory structure. Let me read the skill file to understand what it does and then determine if it's relevant.\n\nThe skill is located at `/home/peter/.openclaw/workspace/skills/context-anchor/SKILL.md` - wait, the user wrote `/home/peter/` but based on the environment, it should be `/home/pete/`. Let me check the correct path. Looking at the available skills in the system message, I see:\n\n```\n<skill>\n<name>context-anchor</name>\n<description>Recover from context compaction by scanning memory files and surfacing where you left off. Use when waking up fresh, after compaction, or when you feel lost about what you were doing.</description>\n<location>~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/context-anchor/SKILL.md</location>\n</skill>\n```\n\nSo the path should be `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/context-anchor/SKILL.md` which resolves to `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/skills/context-anchor/SKILL.md`.\n\nLet me read this","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"  functions.read:3","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/skills/context-anchor/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":22592,"output":271,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":22863,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771846976482}}
{"type":"message","id":"b4963825","parentId":"30fecf22","timestamp":"2026-02-23T11:43:42.742Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"  functions.read:3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: context-anchor\nversion: 1.0.0\ndescription: Recover from context compaction by scanning memory files and surfacing where you left off. Use when waking up fresh, after compaction, or when you feel lost about what you were doing.\n---\n\n# Context Anchor Skill\n\nHelps agents recover context after compaction by scanning memory files and generating a \"here's where you are\" briefing.\n\n## Why This Exists\n\nContext compaction loses memory. Files survive. But after waking up fresh, you need to:\n1. Know what you were working on\n2. See decisions that were made\n3. Find open loops that need closing\n4. Get oriented fast\n\nThis skill automates that recovery.\n\n---\n\n## Quick Start\n\n```bash\n# Full briefing (default)\n./scripts/anchor.sh\n\n# Just show current task\n./scripts/anchor.sh --task\n\n# Just show active context files\n./scripts/anchor.sh --active\n\n# Just show recent decisions\n./scripts/anchor.sh --decisions\n\n# Show open loops / questions\n./scripts/anchor.sh --loops\n\n# Scan specific number of days back\n./scripts/anchor.sh --days 3\n```\n\n---\n\n## What It Scans\n\n| Source | What It Extracts |\n|--------|------------------|\n| `memory/current-task.md` | Current task status, blockers, next steps |\n| `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` | Recent daily logs (last 2 days by default) |\n| `context/active/*.md` | In-progress task files |\n| Daily logs | Decisions (lines with \"Decision:\", \"Decided:\", \"вң…\") |\n| Daily logs | Open loops (lines with \"?\", \"TODO:\", \"Blocker:\", \"Need to\") |\n\n---\n\n## Output Format\n\nThe script outputs a structured briefing:\n\n```\nв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n                    CONTEXT ANCHOR\n              Where You Left Off\nв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n\nрҹ“Ӣ CURRENT TASK\nв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n[Contents of memory/current-task.md or \"No current task set\"]\n\nрҹ“Ӯ ACTIVE CONTEXT FILES\nв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\nвҖў context/active/project-name.md (updated 2h ago)\n  в””в”Җ First line preview...\n\nрҹҺҜ RECENT DECISIONS (last 2 days)\nв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n[2026-01-30] Decision: Use Cloudflare Pages for hosting\n[2026-01-30] вң… Completed email capture setup\n\nвқ“ OPEN LOOPS\nв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ\n[2026-01-30] Need to enable SFTP on NAS\n[2026-01-30] TODO: Create Product Hunt account\n\nв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ\n```\n\n---\n\n## Integration with AGENTS.md\n\nAdd to your \"Every Session\" routine:\n\n```markdown\n## Every Session\n\nBefore doing anything else:\n1. Run `./skills/context-anchor/scripts/anchor.sh` for orientation\n2. Read `SOUL.md` вҖ” this is who you are\n3. Read `USER.md` вҖ” this is who you're helping\n...\n```\n\nOr use it manually when you feel lost about context.\n\n---\n\n## Customization\n\n### Change workspace root\n\n```bash\nWORKSPACE=/path/to/workspace ./scripts/anchor.sh\n```\n\n### Change days to scan\n\n```bash\n./scripts/anchor.sh --days 5  # Scan 5 days back\n```\n\n---\n\n## No Dependencies\n\nPure bash. Uses only:\n- `find`, `grep`, `head`, `tail`, `date`, `stat`\n- Works on macOS and Linux\n- No external tools required\n\n---\n\n## When to Use\n\n- **Session start**: Quick orientation on what's happening\n- **After compaction**: Recover lost context\n- **Feeling lost**: \"Wait, what was I doing?\"\n- **Handoff**: Show another agent where things stand\n- **Daily review**: See what decisions were made\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771847022738}}
{"type":"message","id":"37c03513","parentId":"b4963825","timestamp":"2026-02-23T11:45:41.036Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" Now let me analyze this skill in relation to my current QMD memory structure.\n\nFrom what I read in MEMORY.md, I have a QMD (Queryable Memory Documents) Hierarchical Memory System set up:\n\n1. **Status:** Fully operational - Version 1.0.6\n2. **Index:** `~/.cache/qmd/index.sqlite` (3.3 MB)\n3. **Documents:** 8 indexed, 24 vector chunks\n4. **MCP Server:** Running at `http://localhost:8181/mcp`\n\nThe QMD system has 5 collections:\n- **system** (3 files) - Gateway, auth, cron, config\n- **projects** (0 files) - YouTube, GitHub, CRM (structure ready)\n- **daily** (1 file) - Session notes, conversations\n- **skills** (0 files) - Built-in and custom skills\n- **reference** (4 files) - WHOAMI, UNDERSTANDING-PRD, QMD guides\n\nThe context-anchor skill:\n- Scans `memory/current-task.md` for current task status\n- Scans `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` for recent daily logs\n- Scans `context/active/*.md` for in-progress task files\n- Extracts decisions and open loops from daily logs\n\nGiven that:\n1. I have QMD set up which already provides semantic search capabilities\n2. The context-anchor skill is designed for a flat file structure (daily logs in `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md`)\n3. My QMD system uses a hierarchical collection-based approach (system/, daily/, reference/, projects/, skills/)\n\nThe context-anchor skill is **partially applicable but has overlaps and differences** with my QMD setup:\n\n**Overlap:**\n- Both help with context recovery\n- Both scan memory files\n\n**Differences:**\n- context-anchor uses file-based scanning with bash/grep (flat structure)\n- QMD uses semantic vector search with BM25 + embeddings + reranking\n\n\n- context-anchor extracts structured data like decisions and open loops manually\n- QMD provides query-based retrieval with collection filtering\n\nThe skills serve distinct but complementary purposes. While context-anchor offers a structured briefing from flat files, QMD enables sophisticated semantic search across collections. I could potentially integrate both, using context-anchor for quick overviews and QMD for deep information retrieval.\n\nThe key consideration is whether QMD's generic search capability can effectively extract specific insights like decisions and open loops. If QMD lacks this granular parsing, context-anchor's specialized extraction might provide valuable additional functionality.\n\nComparing the two approaches reveals subtle but important nuances. Context anchoring offers speed and structured extraction, while QMD provides semantic depth. The decision hinges on whether the specific pattern recognition for decisions and TODOs matters more than comprehensive retrieval capabilities.\n\nMaintaining both skills creates a robust memory management strategy, allowing quick context recovery alongside the more sophisticated QMD","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" Based on my analysis of the `context-anchor` skill and my current **QMD Hierarchical Memory System**, here's my assessment:\n\n## Applicability: **Partially Applicable with Key Differences**\n\n### What context-anchor does:\n- Scans flat files: `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md`, `memory/current-task.md`, `context/active/*.md`\n- Extracts structured data: decisions (lines with \"Decision:\", \"вң…\") and open loops (\"TODO:\", \"Blocker:\", \"?\")\n- Generates a formatted \"where you left off\" briefing via bash script\n- Uses grep/head/tail for pattern matching\n\n### My QMD setup:\n- **Hybrid search**: BM25 (exact) + vectors (semantic) + LLM reranking\n- **Hierarchical collections**: `system/`, `daily/`, `reference/`, `projects/`, `skills/`\n- **Recency tiering**: Documents automatically weighted by date\n- **Query expansion**: LLM generates search variants\n\n### The Verdict:\n\n| Capability | context-anchor | QMD | Winner |\n|------------|---------------|-----|--------|\n| **Speed** | Fast (grep) | Slower (vectors) | context-anchor |\n| **Decision/TODO extraction** | Hardcoded patterns | Generic semantic search | context-anchor |\n| **Deep semantic recall** | No | Yes | QMD |\n| **\"What was I doing?\" queries** | Structured briefing | Natural language search | **Both** |\n| **Collection filtering** | No | Yes (`-c daily`) | QMD |\n\n### Recommendation:\n\n**Keep both.** They're complementary:\n\n- **QMD** is my primary memory system for complex, contextual queries (\"what did we decide about the cron job timeout?\")\n- **context-anchor** is useful for quick orientation at session start вҖ” especially its **pattern extraction** for decisions and open loops, which QMD doesn't natively surface\n\nI *could* replicate the decision/open-loop extraction with QMD queries, but the skill's pre-built formatted output is convenient. Given it has **no dependencies** (pure bash), there's no cost to keeping it.\n\n**One caveat**: The skill expects flat `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` files. My QMD uses `daily/2026/02/18.md` structure. I'd need to either:\n1. Update the script's file path patterns, or\n2. Maintain compatibility symlinks\n\nWant me to adapt the skill for QMD compatibility, or document it in MEMORY.md as a secondary tool?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":23624,"output":1113,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24737,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771847022743}}
{"type":"message","id":"1a9c6c55","parentId":"37c03513","timestamp":"2026-02-23T11:49:22.451Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"9cfb0737-94f7-48a3-a2ba-d6c52ae8c9b8\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"sender\": \"gateway-client\"\n}\n```\n\n[Mon 2026-02-23 19:49 GMT+8] please update the `context-anchor` skill to match the memory file naming/format as the current QMD system so that both systems can coexist together to help you to efficiently recall past events."}],"timestamp":1771847362447}}
{"type":"message","id":"7adfd82c","parentId":"1a9c6c55","timestamp":"2026-02-23T11:50:34.830Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" The user wants me to update the context-anchor skill to work with the QMD memory file naming/format. Let me check the current structure of the context-anchor skill and understand what needs to be changed.\n\nFrom what I read:\n1. context-anchor expects: `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (flat structure)\n2. QMD uses: `daily/2026/02/18.md` (hierarchical structure)\n\nI need to:\n1. Read the current anchor.sh script to understand its structure\n2. Update it to handle the QMD hierarchical path format\n3. Make sure it can still work with both formats or exclusively with QMD format as requested\n4. Update SKILL.md if needed\n\nLet me first explore the skill structure and","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" I'll update the `context-anchor` skill to work with your QMD hierarchical structure. Let me first examine the current script"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"  functions.read:4","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/skills/context-anchor/scripts/anchor.sh"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"  functions.exec:5","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/skills/context-anchor/"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":24025,"output":243,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24268,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771847362450}}
{"type":"message","id":"d53da76f","parentId":"7adfd82c","timestamp":"2026-02-23T11:50:34.849Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"  functions.read:4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/bin/bash\n#\n# context-anchor: Recover context after compaction\n# Scans memory files and generates a \"here's where you are\" briefing\n#\n\nset -e\n\n# Configuration\nWORKSPACE=\"${WORKSPACE:-$(cd \"$(dirname \"$0\")/../../..\" && pwd)}\"\nMEMORY_DIR=\"$WORKSPACE/memory\"\nCONTEXT_DIR=\"$WORKSPACE/context/active\"\nDAYS_BACK=\"${DAYS_BACK:-2}\"\n\n# Colors (disabled if not a terminal)\nif [ -t 1 ]; then\n    BOLD='\\033[1m'\n    DIM='\\033[2m'\n    RESET='\\033[0m'\n    BLUE='\\033[34m'\n    GREEN='\\033[32m'\n    YELLOW='\\033[33m'\n    CYAN='\\033[36m'\nelse\n    BOLD=''\n    DIM=''\n    RESET=''\n    BLUE=''\n    GREEN=''\n    YELLOW=''\n    CYAN=''\nfi\n\n# Parse arguments\nSHOW_ALL=true\nSHOW_TASK=false\nSHOW_ACTIVE=false\nSHOW_DECISIONS=false\nSHOW_LOOPS=false\n\nwhile [[ $# -gt 0 ]]; do\n    case $1 in\n        --task)\n            SHOW_ALL=false\n            SHOW_TASK=true\n            shift\n            ;;\n        --active)\n            SHOW_ALL=false\n            SHOW_ACTIVE=true\n            shift\n            ;;\n        --decisions)\n            SHOW_ALL=false\n            SHOW_DECISIONS=true\n            shift\n            ;;\n        --loops)\n            SHOW_ALL=false\n            SHOW_LOOPS=true\n            shift\n            ;;\n        --days)\n            DAYS_BACK=\"$2\"\n            shift 2\n            ;;\n        --help|-h)\n            echo \"Usage: anchor.sh [OPTIONS]\"\n            echo \"\"\n            echo \"Options:\"\n            echo \"  --task       Show only current task\"\n            echo \"  --active     Show only active context files\"\n            echo \"  --decisions  Show only recent decisions\"\n            echo \"  --loops      Show only open loops\"\n            echo \"  --days N     Scan N days back (default: 2)\"\n            echo \"  --help       Show this help\"\n            exit 0\n            ;;\n        *)\n            echo \"Unknown option: $1\"\n            exit 1\n            ;;\n    esac\ndone\n\n# Helper: print header\nheader() {\n    echo -e \"${BOLD}${BLUE}$1${RESET}\"\n    echo -e \"${DIM}в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җ${RESET}\"\n}\n\n# Helper: relative time\nrelative_time() {\n    local file=\"$1\"\n    local now=$(date +%s)\n    local mod\n    \n    # macOS vs Linux stat\n    if [[ \"$OSTYPE\" == \"darwin\"* ]]; then\n        mod=$(stat -f %m \"$file\" 2>/dev/null || echo 0)\n    else\n        mod=$(stat -c %Y \"$file\" 2>/dev/null || echo 0)\n    fi\n    \n    local diff=$((now - mod))\n    \n    if [ $diff -lt 60 ]; then\n        echo \"just now\"\n    elif [ $diff -lt 3600 ]; then\n        echo \"$((diff / 60))m ago\"\n    elif [ $diff -lt 86400 ]; then\n        echo \"$((diff / 3600))h ago\"\n    else\n        echo \"$((diff / 86400))d ago\"\n    fi\n}\n\n# Helper: get daily files for last N days\nget_daily_files() {\n    local files=()\n    for i in $(seq 0 $((DAYS_BACK - 1))); do\n        if [[ \"$OSTYPE\" == \"darwin\"* ]]; then\n            local date_str=$(date -v-${i}d +%Y-%m-%d)\n        else\n            local date_str=$(date -d \"-$i days\" +%Y-%m-%d)\n        fi\n        local file=\"$MEMORY_DIR/${date_str}.md\"\n        if [ -f \"$file\" ]; then\n            files+=(\"$file\")\n        fi\n    done\n    echo \"${files[@]}\"\n}\n\n# Section: Current Task\nshow_current_task() {\n    header \"рҹ“Ӣ CURRENT TASK\"\n    \n    local task_file=\"$MEMORY_DIR/current-task.md\"\n    if [ -f \"$task_file\" ]; then\n        echo -e \"${DIM}($(relative_time \"$task_file\"))${RESET}\"\n        echo \"\"\n        cat \"$task_file\"\n    else\n        echo -e \"${DIM}No current task set (memory/current-task.md not found)${RESET}\"\n    fi\n    echo \"\"\n}\n\n# Section: Active Context Files\nshow_active_context() {\n    header \"рҹ“Ӯ ACTIVE CONTEXT FILES\"\n    \n    if [ ! -d \"$CONTEXT_DIR\" ]; then\n        echo -e \"${DIM}No context/active/ directory${RESET}\"\n        echo \"\"\n        return\n    fi\n    \n    local found=false\n    for file in \"$CONTEXT_DIR\"/*.md; do\n        [ -e \"$file\" ] || continue\n        found=true\n        local name=$(basename \"$file\")\n        local age=$(relative_time \"$file\")\n        local preview=$(head -n 5 \"$file\" | grep -v '^#' | grep -v '^$' | head -n 1)\n        \n        echo -e \"${GREEN}вҖў ${name}${RESET} ${DIM}(${age})${RESET}\"\n        if [ -n \"$preview\" ]; then\n            echo -e \"  ${DIM}в””в”Җ ${preview:0:70}...${RESET}\"\n        fi\n    done\n    \n    if [ \"$found\" = false ]; then\n        echo -e \"${DIM}No active context files${RESET}\"\n    fi\n    echo \"\"\n}\n\n# Section: Recent Decisions\nshow_decisions() {\n    header \"рҹҺҜ RECENT DECISIONS (last $DAYS_BACK days)\"\n    \n    local files=($(get_daily_files))\n    local found=false\n    \n    for file in \"${files[@]}\"; do\n        local date=$(basename \"$file\" .md)\n        \n        # Look for decision patterns\n        grep -n -i -E \"(^|\\s)(decision:|decided:|chose:|picked:|went with|вң….*completed|вң….*done|вң….*finished)\" \"$file\" 2>/dev/null | while read -r line; do\n            found=true\n            # Extract just the content, clean it up\n            local content=$(echo \"$line\" | sed 's/^[0-9]*://' | sed 's/^[ -]*//')\n            echo -e \"${CYAN}[$date]${RESET} $content\"\n        done\n    done\n    \n    if [ \"$found\" = false ]; then\n        # Check if we actually found nothing\n        local any_decisions=false\n        for file in \"${files[@]}\"; do\n            if grep -q -i -E \"(decision:|decided:|вң…)\" \"$file\" 2>/dev/null; then\n                any_decisions=true\n                break\n            fi\n        done\n        if [ \"$any_decisions\" = false ]; then\n            echo -e \"${DIM}No explicit decisions found in recent logs${RESET}\"\n        fi\n    fi\n    echo \"\"\n}\n\n# Section: Open Loops\nshow_loops() {\n    header \"вқ“ OPEN LOOPS & TODO\"\n    \n    local files=($(get_daily_files))\n    local task_file=\"$MEMORY_DIR/current-task.md\"\n    local found=false\n    \n    # Check daily files for open items\n    for file in \"${files[@]}\"; do\n        local date=$(basename \"$file\" .md)\n        \n        # Look for open loop patterns (questions, TODOs, blockers, unchecked items)\n        grep -n -E \"(^|\\s)(\\?$|TODO:|FIXME:|Blocker:|Need to|needs to|should|waiting for|- \\[ \\])\" \"$file\" 2>/dev/null | \\\n        grep -v -E \"(вң…|\\[x\\]|\\[X\\])\" | while read -r line; do\n            found=true\n            local content=$(echo \"$line\" | sed 's/^[0-9]*://' | sed 's/^[ -]*//')\n            echo -e \"${YELLOW}[$date]${RESET} $content\"\n        done\n    done\n    \n    # Check current-task.md for unchecked items\n    if [ -f \"$task_file\" ]; then\n        grep -n -E \"^- \\[ \\]\" \"$task_file\" 2>/dev/null | while read -r line; do\n            found=true\n            local content=$(echo \"$line\" | sed 's/^[0-9]*://' | sed 's/^- \\[ \\] //')\n            echo -e \"${YELLOW}[current-task]${RESET} $content\"\n        done\n    fi\n    \n    if [ \"$found\" = false ]; then\n        echo -e \"${DIM}No obvious open loops found${RESET}\"\n    fi\n    echo \"\"\n}\n\n# Main output\nmain() {\n    if [ \"$SHOW_ALL\" = true ]; then\n        echo \"\"\n        echo -e \"${BOLD}в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ${RESET}\"\n        echo -e \"${BOLD}                    CONTEXT ANCHOR${RESET}\"\n        echo -e \"${BOLD}              Where You Left Off${RESET}\"\n        echo -e \"${BOLD}в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ${RESET}\"\n        echo \"\"\n        \n        show_current_task\n        show_active_context\n        show_decisions\n        show_loops\n        \n        echo -e \"${BOLD}в•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җв•җ${RESET}\"\n        echo \"\"\n    else\n        [ \"$SHOW_TASK\" = true ] && show_current_task\n        [ \"$SHOW_ACTIVE\" = true ] && show_active_context\n        [ \"$SHOW_DECISIONS\" = true ] && show_decisions\n        [ \"$SHOW_LOOPS\" = true ] && show_loops\n    fi\n}\n\nmain\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771847434841}}
