{"type":"message","id":"aa3e7257","parentId":"a097ddaa","timestamp":"2026-02-23T12:57:03.191Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"    Done! The context-anchor skill has been updated to support both QMD hierarchical memory structure (daily/YYYY/MM/DD.md) and flat structure (YYYY-MM-DD.md). The script now:\n\n1. Checks QMD paths first when looking for daily memos\n2. Falls back to flat paths if QMD version doesn't exist\n3. Properly extracts dates from both filepath formats\n4. Maintains backward compatibility with existing flat files\n\nLet","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" Done! I've updated the `context-anchor` skill to work with both memory structures.\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### `scripts/anchor.sh`\n- **Version bump**: 1.0.0 вҶ’ 1.1.0\n- **New function** `extract_date_from_path()`: Parses both formats:\n  - QMD: `daily/2026/02/23.md` вҶ’ `2026-02-23`\n  - Flat: `2026-02-23.md` вҶ’ `2026-02-23`\n- **Updated** `get_daily_files()`: Checks QMD path first, falls back to flat\n- **Logic**: Uses regex to detect hierarchical paths vs flat filenames\n\n### `SKILL.md`\n- Updated version and description\n- Added memory structure support section documenting the dual-mode behavior\n\n## How It Works Now\n\nWhen scanning for daily logs, the script:\n1. **Prefers QMD**: Checks `memory/daily/2026/02/23.md` first\n2. **Falls back**: Uses `memory/2026-02-23.md` if QMD file doesn't exist\n3. **Dedupes**: Same date won't appear twice (defensive)\n\nThis lets both systems coexist вҖ” old flat files continue working while new QMD entries take precedence."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":35775,"output":371,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36146,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771851323000}}
