{"type":"message","id":"3e110a3c","parentId":"c90dafed","timestamp":"2026-02-23T13:10:45.844Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" The user wants me to:\n1. Meticulously review the whole new memory system setup\n2. Ensure everything is in order and updated correctly\n3. Record this new memory system in my working logic so it's automatically executed and used\n\nLet me think about what the \"new memory system\" comprises:\n\n1. **QMD Hierarchical Memory System** - Already set up and documented in MEMORY.md\n   - Collections: system, daily, projects, skills, reference\n   - Hierarchical paths: daily/2026/02/23.md\n   - Hybrid search: BM25 + vectors + reranking\n   - Available commands: qmd search, qmd vsearch, qmd query, qmd get\n\n2. **Curated Skills Repository** - Just discovered at `/home/project/openclaw/curated_skills`\n   - 791 security-vetted skills\n   - 20 categories\n   - Search via find-skill.sh or skills-index.json\n   - TrustSkill v3.1 for security scanning\n\n3. **Context-Anchor Skill** - Just updated to work with both memory structures\n   - Now supports both flat (YYYY-MM-DD.md) and QMD hierarchical (daily/YYYY/MM/DD.md) formats\n   - Version 1.1.0\n\nI need to:\n1. Review the entire memory system setup\n2. Check if everything is properly configured\n3. Update my working logic/AGENTS.md to automatically use this system\n4. Document this in MEMORY.md\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" I'll conduct a thorough review of the memory system setup and ensure it's properly integrated into my working logic."},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.read:20","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.exec:21","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.exec:22","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"qmd status 2>/dev/null || echo \"QMD not in PATH\""}}